com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.name: AppId
com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.description: 1 byte for specifying the command-target application on SPOT.

com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.name: SK
com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.description: 8+8 binary bytes representing the SK (left and right components encrypted separately).

com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.name: crc32
com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.description: 4 bytes for CRC32 calculated on cleartext SK + 4 random bytes for 8-bytes alignment

com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.name: rem
com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.description: 1 bytes SK-encrypted counter which specifies the number of padding bytes (not including itself) to be discarded before APDU and crc16. This counter is required to be in the range [1,8]. Value zeronot allowed.

com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.name: dum
com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.description: 1 to 8 random bytes (SK-encrypted) used to align the length of the encrypted section to 8 bytes multiple.

com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.name: Sign
com.gilbarco.globaltools.mgp.domain.exte.description: CRC32. It allows to verify the release of the local application on SPOT
